sentences: Evan David Taubenfeld (born June 27, 1983) is an American singer-songwriter, best known for being Avril Lavigne's lead guitarist, music director and frequent collaborator.
Taubenfeld's debut album, Welcome to the Blacklist Club, was released on May 18, 2010 on Warner Records.
He has two siblings, a younger brother named Drew (b. 1984), who is the guitarist in Selena Gomez & the Scene, and a younger sister, Annie (b. 1990).

In 2010, he performed "Complicated" and "Girlfriend" acoustically with Lavigne and her band member, Jim McGorman.
On Goodbye Lullaby from 2011, he co-wrote three songs, performed vocals on the bridge of "Push", along with playing in several instruments, and doing engineering and producing work on the album.
